## Commercial Licensing

Commercial licensing is available separately from the copyright holder. A
commercial license may include financial terms, attribution terms, community
benefit commitments, deployment limits, support, private features, or other
conditions agreed in writing.

The intent is simple: personal, educational, nonprofit, research, evaluation,
and small-business use should be able to happen without friction; large
commercial use should ask, pay fairly, and leave room for the work to benefit
the communities it came from.

